# Sidewalk and Refreshments - Inventory System Build Plan
## Developer Checklist

**Project:** Sidewalk Inventory System (Django)
**Location:** Dinagat Island
**Last Updated:** May 30, 2026

> **How to use this checklist:** Work through phases in order. Check off each item as it's completed. Do not proceed to the next phase until all items in the current phase are done.

---

## PHASE 0 - Environment Fix (Do This First!)

> The `ImportError: Couldn't import Django` error must be resolved before anything else.

- [ ] Open terminal in project root (`restaurant_inventory/`)
- [ ] Activate virtual environment:
  - Windows: `.venv\Scripts\activate`
  - Mac/Linux: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- [ ] Confirm Django is installed: `pip show django`
- [ ] If not installed: `pip install django`
- [x] Run check: `python manage.py check` - should return **System check identified no issues**
- [x] Run dev server: `python manage.py runserver` - confirm it starts without errors
- [x] Create a `requirements.txt`: `pip freeze > requirements.txt`

---

## PHASE 1 - Project Structure & Configuration

- [x] Verify `config/settings.py` has correct `INSTALLED_APPS` (includes `inventory`)
- [x] Verify `DATABASES` is configured (SQLite default is fine for MVP)
- [x] Set `DEBUG = True` for development, document plan to set `False` for production
- [x] Set `ALLOWED_HOSTS` appropriately (e.g., `['localhost', '127.0.0.1']`)
- [x] Confirm `urls.py` at project level routes to `inventory` app URLs
- [x] Confirm `inventory/urls.py` exists and has all routes defined
- [x] Confirm `templates/inventory/` folder structure matches Django template loader config
- [x] Run `python manage.py migrate` - all migrations applied cleanly

