## PHASE 2 - Data Models

- [x] **Category model** - fields: `name`, `slug` (optional), `created_at`
- [x] **InventoryItem model** - fields: `name`, `category (FK)`, `unit`, `quantity`, `reorder_threshold`, `created_at`, `updated_at`
- [x] **StockTransaction model** - fields: `item (FK)`, `transaction_type (in/out)`, `quantity`, `date`, `note`, `created_at`
- [x] **MenuItem model** - fields: `name`, `description`, `price`, `category`, `is_available`, `linked_item (FK nullable)`
- [x] Add `__str__` methods to all models
- [x] Add `is_low_stock` property to `InventoryItem` (returns `True` if `quantity <= reorder_threshold`)
- [x] Create and apply migrations: `python manage.py makemigrations && python manage.py migrate`
- [x] Register all models in `admin.py`
- [x] Seed at least 5 test items via Django admin or fixture

